@vossiewulfIt Seems you are running out of memory. You have too many Mods installed.

That is an older version of Module manager you are running there. for 1.3 you should be on version 2.8 I believe?

Also interesting to note that it's in your (x86) folder of windows, where the 32 bit stuff lives. Also it looks like it's trying to run KSP in 32bit compatibility mode: 

Environment Info
Win32NT 7FFFFFFFFFFFFFFF  Args: KSP_x64.exe

Try taking out the KSP folder from its current directory and placing it into the Program Files folder? Then run it from there?

16 hours ago, tmccreight651 said:

hey guys, so ive asked about my problems with this mod, those being that the game crashes when i try to load it with this mod installed, so i finally figured out how to share the game logs, so here are my logs. all help appreciated

Hey, so I spot a number of things in your log that look fishy:

  1. You're running KSP.exe (32-bit) and not KSP_x64.exe (64-bit) thus limiting your available memory
  2. You're running Firespitter v7.3.6212.36331, the latest version seems to be v7.6 here
  3. You've got 2 versions of module manager running ModuleManager.2.7.1 and ModuleManager.2.8.0. Only use the latest, remove the old one

Thank you @Cheesecake and @steedcrugeon for stepping in to help. I'm still swamped at work, so my KSP time has been scarce

As far as I know, unless you have explicitly configured it, Steam will launch 32-bit by default. It is not broken, just the default launch option.
